1. # **Introduction** {#introduction}

   1. ## ***Purpose*** {#purpose}

This document provides a detailed design for "OJTech," an AI-driven "OJT Management Portal with Job Matching" developed by the College of Computer Studies at Cebu Institute of Technology University. The system is designed to connect Computer Studies students with relevant job opportunities by leveraging advanced technologies and a modular, scalable architecture. It outlines the architectural framework, individual components, and technical implementation details necessary to fulfill the requirements specified in the Software Requirements Specifications for the OJT Management Portal with Job Matching.

2. ## ***Scope*** {#scope}

The system is a **web-based platform** with three main portals:

* **Student Portal**: CV management and job matching.  
* **Employer Portal**: Job postings and candidate recommendations.  
* **Admin Dashboard**: System management.

It leverages **Next.js, Supabase, and AI APIs** to ensure a scalable and secure solution.

3. ## ***Definitions and Acronyms*** {#definitions-and-acronyms}

| Acronym | Definition |
| :---- | ----- |
| **AI:** |  Artificial Intelligence – Used for job matching and resume analysis. |
| **CV:** | Curriculum Vitae – Student-uploaded resume file. |
| **OAuth:** | Open standard authentication protocol (GitHub, Gmail). |
| **Supabase:** | Backend-as-a-Service platform for database, authentication, and storage. |
| **Next.js:** | JavaScript framework for frontend development. |
| **REST API:** | Representational State Transfer Application Programming Interface. |

   4. ## ***References*** {#references}

2. # **Architectural Design** {#architectural-design}

*Block diagram showing all components of the system including frameworks, libraries, APIs and other technologies used in the front and back ends.*

*The system follows a **client-server architecture** with a modular structure. Below is a textual description of the block diagram showing all components:*

***Block Diagram Description:***

* ***Client Layer:***  
  * ***Next.js Frontend:** Built with shadcn UI and Tailwind CSS for responsive design.*  
  * *Connected to three portals: Student Portal, Employer Portal, and Admin Dashboard.*  
* ***Server Layer:***  
  * ***Supabase Backend:** Handles PostgreSQL database, authentication, and CV storage.*  
  * *Integrates with external **OpenAI API** or **Gemini** for AI-driven job matching.*  
* ***Communication:** RESTful APIs over HTTPS connect the frontend and backend.*  
* ***External APIs:** OAuth (GitHub, Gmail) for authentication, OpenAI for resume analysis.*

***Technologies Used:***

***Frontend:** Next.js, shadcn UI, Tailwind CSS.*

***Backend:** Supabase (PostgreSQL, Authentication, Storage).*

***AI:** OpenAI API, Gemini.*

***Security:** OAuth 2.0.*

3. # **Detailed Design** {#detailed-design}

### ***Module 1*** {#module-1}

#### ***1.1 User Login***

* User Interface Design

  * A login page with buttons for "Login with GitHub" and "Login with Gmail."  
  * Redirects to role-specific dashboards (Student, Employer, Admin) post-login.


* Front-end component(s)

  * Component Name:LoginButton

    * **Description and Purpose:** Renders OAuth login buttons and handles redirection.

    * **Component Type or Format:** React component (JSX).

* Back-end component(s)

  * Component Name:AuthService

    * **Description and Purpose:** Manages OAuth token exchange and user session creation.

    * **Component Type or Format:** Supabase Authentication API wrapper (JavaScript).

* Object-Oriented Components

  **Class Diagram Description:**

* User class: Attributes (id, email, role, oauth\_token).  
* AuthService class: Methods (loginWithOAuth, validateToken).

![][image1]

**Sequence Diagram Description:**

* User clicks "Login with GitHub."  
* Frontend redirects to GitHub OAuth.  
* GitHub returns token to AuthService.  
* AuthService validates token and assigns role.  
* Frontend redirects to appropriate dashboard.

#### ***![][image2]***

* Data Design

  * Table: Users (id (PK), email, role, oauth\_token)

  


#### ***1.2 Student Job Matching***

* User Interface Design

  * A drag-and-drop file upload area for CVs (PDF/DOCX).  
  * Displays AI-generated job recommendations in a card layout.


* Front-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** CVUploader

* **Description and Purpose:** Handles CV file upload and displays upload status.  
* **Component Type or Format:** React component (JSX).

  **Component Name:** JobRecommendations

* **Description and Purpose:** Renders a list of matched jobs with details.  
* **Component Type or Format:** React component (JSX).  
* Back-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** CVProcessor

* **Description and Purpose:** Extracts skills from CV using OpenAI API and stores them.  
* **Component Type or Format:** JavaScript function (Node.js).

  **Component Name:** JobMatcher

* **Description and Purpose:** Matches CV skills to job listings using a scoring algorithm.  
* **Component Type or Format:** JavaScript function (Node.js).  
* Object-Oriented Components


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


**Class Diagram Description:**

* CV class: Attributes (id, user\_id, file\_url, skills (JSON)).  
* Job class: Attributes (id, employer\_id, title, required\_skills (JSON)).  
* Matcher class: Methods (extractSkills, calculateMatchScore).


**![][image3]**

**Sequence Diagram Description:**

* Student uploads CV via CVUploader.  
  * Frontend sends file to CVProcessor.  
  * CVProcessor calls OpenAI API to extract skills.  
  * JobMatcher compares skills to job listings.  
  * Frontend displays results in JobRecommendations.

![][image4]

* Data Design

  **ERD/Schema:**

* Table: CVs (id (PK), user\_id (FK), file\_url, skills (JSON), upload\_date).  
* Table: Jobs (id (PK), employer\_id (FK), title, required\_skills (JSON)).  
* Table: Matches (id (PK), cv\_id (FK), job\_id (FK), match\_score).

### ***Module 2*** {#module-2}

#### ***2.1 Resume Optimization***

* User Interface Design

  A section showing AI-generated suggestions (e.g., "Add specific skills like React").

* Front-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** ResumeTips

* **Description and Purpose:** Displays optimization suggestions from AI.  
* **Component Type or Format:** React component (JSX).


* Back-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** ResumeAnalyzer

* **Description and Purpose:** Uses OpenAI API to analyze CV and suggest improvements.  
* **Component Type or Format:** JavaScript function (Node.js).


* Object-Oriented Components

  **Class Diagram Description:**

* CVAnalyzer class: Methods (analyzeCV, generateTips).

  ![][image5]


  

  **Sequence Diagram Description:**

* Student views CV analysis via ResumeTips.  
* Frontend calls ResumeAnalyzer.  
* ResumeAnalyzer sends CV to OpenAI API.  
* API returns suggestions; frontend renders them.

![][image6]

* Data Design

  * Reuse CVs table from 2.1; no additional schema needed.

* Front-end component(s)

* Back-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** JobService

* **Description and Purpose:** Saves job listing to the database.  
* **Component Type or Format:** JavaScript function (Node.js).


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


  

* Object-Oriented Components

  **Class Diagram Description:**

* Job class: Attributes (id, employer\_id, title, description, required\_skills).  
* JobService class: Methods (createJob, validateJobData).

  ![][image7]


  


  


  **Sequence Diagram Description:**

* Employer fills JobForm.  
* Frontend sends data to JobService.

### ***Module 3***

#### ***3.1 View Candidate Matches***

* User Interface Design

  A table listing AI-recommended candidates with skills and contact options.

* Front-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** CandidateList

* **Description and Purpose:** Displays matched candidates for a job.  
* **Component Type or Format:** React component (JSX).


* Back-end component(s)

  **Component Name:** CandidateMatcher

* **Description and Purpose:** Retrieves and ranks candidates based on job skills.  
* **Component Type or Format:** JavaScript function (Node.js).


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


  


* **Object-Oriented Components**

  Class Diagram Description:

* Match class: Attributes (id, cv\_id, job\_id, match\_score).  
* CandidateMatcher class: Methods (fetchMatches, rankCandidates).

  ![][image9]

		Sequence Diagram Description:

* Employer views job matches via CandidateList.  
* Frontend queries CandidateMatcher.  
* CandidateMatcher retrieves matches from database.  
* Frontend renders ranked candidates.

![][image10]

* Data Design

  * Reuse Matches table from 2.1; no additional schema needed.
